                    "Travel, lodging, meals, or any other cost for a spouse, partner, family member, or other companion accompanying the employee on a business trip is not reimbursable, including any incremental cost of upgrading a hotel room from single to double occupancy to accommodate a companion. Where a companion travels on the same itinerary, the employee is responsible for identifying and paying the marginal cost attributable to the companion.",
                    "Personal entertainment such as movies, streaming rentals, spa services, gym or fitness charges beyond a hotel's included facilities, golf outings not tied to client entertainment, and sightseeing or tourism activities are not reimbursable. This is distinct from client entertainment, which is reimbursable within the limits described in the Meals and Incidentals subsection and the Contoso Corp Code of Conduct and Business Ethics Policy.",
